Text.string: Got a job for you, Vault Hunter.
Sounds like the COV are killin' each other. Let's help.
I've killed for money, and I've killed for loot. But killin' for two brats who don't care if you live or die? That don't make a lick of sense to me.
Troy! Did you hire the Vault Thief to help you? Wow. That is low, bro. Bet's off.
What?! I would never do that! But, uh—hey, looks like your people are screwed. HA!
At least all the excitement is driving up our subscriber count! People can't get enough of this. Bet's back on!
Good work. Now, there's a whole lotta boom in that bomb. Thinkin' it's about time to send it on down the line to Camp Troy.
Ohhhh, dip! Vault Thief killed Team Tyreen! In your FACE, TY! Heh-heeee! All hail God-King Troy!
“God-King”? Ugh! You know how that sounds, right?

Looks like those ECHOcasting idiots are having a little family spat. Splittin' their followers into teams and makin' 'em kill each other for sport. And if both sides lose, we win. Here, listen to this while you head toward “Camp Tyreen”.
Damn this old railway. Bomb's stuck. Give it a little “ballistic encouragement” to get it movin' again.
Uh oh, Troy! Looks like the Vault Thief's comin' after your team, too! They're gonna get blowed up!
Pfft, no way! Team Troy's got this.
Rootin' for ya, Vault Thief! Just this one time.
Looks like it needs another nudge.
Get that payload movin' again.
It's stuck. Jostle it free with a few bullets.
Get that payload movin' again with a quick shot.
Just give it a little... bullet-push.
What's up, bandit fam? Troy and I have a little bet going. We want to know who you love more! So, go ahead and organize a Team Tyreen...
Ahahahaha! Troooooy! Your team's gonna get totally roasted!
Rrgh—damn it! Come on, Team Troy! Kill that Vault Thief or I'll... feed you to the grogs one limb at a time!
Now clear out that camp and drop the bomb!
Can't you imbeciles do anything right?
Hahahaha! You barely scraped together a team for this bet, and now they're all gonna die! You suck!
All right then. Looks like it's time for the big show, Vault Hunter. Drop that payload and watch the fireworks work their fire.
Yes! Time for a big-ass boom!
Ohohoh, this should be fun.
I do enjoy explosions.
Ohohoho! Yes-yes-yes-yes-yes-YES! Let's blow this sucker!

These whiny brats are just self-obsessed. Musta spent too much time lookin' at themselves in the mirror. That's why they're monsters. Me? I never looked in a mirror once, and I'm doing fine. Just fine.
And a Team Troy!
Hey. Hey, Troy. All your followers are, like, super-duper dead. Just a little FYI.
Ty, the Vault Thief killed BOTH of our teams.
Whoa! Butt-hurt alert. Pthbhthtbhtbth.
Here's hoping the Calypsos keep makin' their followers kill each other over petty bullshit. Makes our job a hell of a lot easier. Pleasure working with you again, “smooth operator”!
Uh... well, it didn't quite “explode”, but I guess that'll do. Can't even trust the COV to make a bomb right. But in any case, both teams are dead, so I'd call it a win. Score one for Team Jakobs.
Come on back when you're ready.
Oooooh, it's comin' real close, Troy!
No! Team Troy, stop the Vault Thief!
Yeah, well... your team's already a bucket of guts, so.
Then, you know, kill each other for our amusement! 'Kay? Whoever's left standing wins Eridium-tier membership! And it better be Team Tyreeeeen!
Hoo-ee. That's some good ol'-fashioned demolition right there. Looks like you got some loot for your trouble, too! And to top it all off, both teams are dead, so I'd call this a win for Team Jakobs!
Now get to killin'!
Byeee!

I got recon says Team Tyreen was planning to drop off a big bad explosive present for Team Troy. Hell, the resistance was gonna do that anyway, so whaddya say we help 'em kill each other? Clear out that camp and take the bomb for Team Jakobs.
Heh—more than happy to help with that.
I never turn down a chance to join in bloodsport.
That's a hell of a bet. Happy to bring it to a bloody end!
COV killing COV? Sounds like a party.
